    "CNN-based dysgraphia diagnosis systemsCNNs are a type of neural network designed for tasks involving multi-dimensional data such as images or time series information.",
    "A CNN comprises several key components or layers, including convolutional layers, pooling layers, fully connected dense layers, and batch normalization layers.",
    "Additionally, there are input and output layers.Convolutional layers form the foundation of deep CNN architectures.",
    "They consist of learnable filters with small receptive fields, responsible for generating feature maps through convolution operations.",
    "To introduce non-linearity into the network, activation functions, also known as transfer functions, are applied after convolution operations."
